content: Fun fast game

A fun, fast game well worth paying for to remove ads. My experience is generally positive, but matches what other reviewers have said about the bot's many "lucky streaks" like going gin after only one card or coming from behind to win after being down 85pts. Sometimes these streaks go on for a while; they usually end when I uninstall the game. Having an option for randomized opponents would definitely make things more interesting.

Which did she discard? The 5 of diamonds. I've seen this before but needed to pay attention to catch it. I have screenshot if interested.
replyContent: Thank you for the input but our games do not cheat. Deals are random and cpu player does not know your cards except using inference and probability as any human player can. Please send screenshots of any play you'd like to query to support@aifactory.co.uk

content: This app is just like playing gin rummy with a real opponent -- if you let your opponent look at your cards on every play and your deck has many multiples of each card. Just discarded that King of Diamonds? No worries, it will turn up again in a few plays. The algorithm very obviously tailors your opponent's play to the cards you're holding. In short, the already screwed up deck is stacked. Not to say it's not enjoyable, it is. Just know the essential random nature of the draw is not random all.
replyContent: Thank you for your review. All deals are random and cpu player cannot see your hand. However, as in real life, it can guess what cards you may need based on your discards and visible pickups. Also if you wait for a card that opponent holds, as in real life, you are likely to lose. Cards may reappear if picked up and later discarded by opponent.

Developer swears it's random, even though over 50 games AI had double the statistical expectation of first card draws (quoted by developer) while I had none. AI plays only to knock ASAP, and is more often than not able to in 5 draws or less regardless of level. Overall a pretty boring Oklahoma Gin game.
replyContent: All deals are random and have nothing to gain from unfair play. In a block test of 1029 games, only 28 games finished after a single card draw, about 2.7%, which is the statistical expectation but randomness means quick draw games may happen at any time. Some AI players knock as early as possible as they have learnt this is the best way to win.

replyContent: I'm afraid you and the other reviewer are mistaken. The app has pure random deals and no access to knowledge of opponent hands. It uses probability and inferences from cards played to estimate opponent hands. The app has been block tested for millions of hands to prove randomness. Us having it cheat would be pointless & degrade player experience.

replyContent: Thank you for your review. We assure you that the decks are shuffled randomly before dealing each hand.
